President Barack Obama announced his intention to nominate Regina M. Benjamin as Surgeon General of the Department of Health and Human Services. President Obama emphasized the importance of healthcare reform and stated that Benjamin understands the urgency of meeting this challenge. Benjamin is the founder and CEO of the Bayou La Batre Rural Health Clinic in Alabama and has held various leadership positions in the medical field. She has been recognized for her contributions to healthcare and has received awards such as the Nelson Mandela Award for Health and Human Rights and the MacArthur Genius Award.